# Summary of AI Agents vs Agentic AI: 

Here is a summary of the difference between an AI Agent and an Agentic AI. 

## AI Agent
- An AI agent is an independent system or tool.
- It is programmed with a pre-defined set of rules and goals.
- It handles only one specific job autonomically.
- For example, it could write your resume. 

## Agentic AI

- Agentic AI is not just one agent.
- Multiple AI agents will collaborate like a team, debating and refining each other to give a collective output.
- As an example, multiple AI agents can work together to get a person hired.
- One agent analyzes the market and researches, a second agent writes custom resumes, and a third agent helps you prepare for interviews.
- Bottom line, Agentic AI is a design approach for handling an entire workflow.
